The paper focuses on energy-efficient beamforming algorithms for distributed sensor/relay networks, which involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The convergence analyses and numerical simulations also suggest a strong emphasis on mathematical optimization and algorithm design, which further supports the likelihood of cs.IT and cs.AI as potential sub-categories.
